sentence: Traders are building a position Tuesday in options on Home Depot ( HD ).
So far, 3,577 contracts of the June 202.50 call have changed hands, against open interest of 556 contracts.
Pricing on these new contracts indicates that they were initiated from the buy side.
IK-> The technicals for HD ($190.73 down $0.63) are bullish with an upward trend.
Look at the July 170/175 bull-put spread for a 23-cent credit.
That's a 4.8% return and the stock has to fall by 8.2% to cause a problem.
